Each instance type is a predefined configuration of:
- vCPUs (virtual CPUs)
- Memory (RAM)
- Storage
- Network performance
Theyâ€™re grouped into families, each optimized for specific workloads. Choosing the right type ensures your app runs efficiently without overpaying.

